<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-11-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="837" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-11-18"><hi rend="italic">November 18,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Dewey telegraphs entire island of Panay in possession of insurgents,
                            except Iloilo, which is defended by 800 Spanish troops. Foreign citizens
                            beg for American protection. Island of Negros has declared independence
                            and desires American protectorate.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>